relatedItem.note: A cut by PAUL McPHARLIN. This Banqueting House, built by Inigo Jones in 1619, was the only part of his design for a huge new palace that was completed, and which escaped a fire in 1698 that destroyed the older section. The Masque of January 1622, was the first of many given in the hall that occupies the upper story. The accoufits of the Treasurer of the Chamber specify, " the upper story [rs by no by] 55 feet in height, to the laying on of the roof... with 14 windows on each side [that is 14 divided by two sides] and one great window at the upper end... with a gallery upon the two sides
